efsextract: efsextract (Extract data form SGI CD or EFS file system)
efsextract:
efsextract: Silicon Graphics (SGI) was a computer company that existed from 1981
efsextract: to 2009. During this period, they shipped software for their
efsextract: computers, sometimes on CD, and often not using the standard ISO9660
efsextract: file system. These discs are instead simply hard disc images pressed
efsextract: to CD. Thus, they have an SGI disk label and an EFS partition.
efsextract:
efsextract: Most systems cannot understand this sort of disc format. This tool was
efsextract: developed to allow non-SGI systems to at least be able to extract
efsextract: files from such discs.
